-- Citi Appoints John Hastings New Chief Executive Officer for Canada Bank
-- Sean B. Pasternak
-- 2010-07-06T13:23:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/citigroup-names-john-hastings-as-chairman-ceo-of-its-canadian-operations.html

          
          
             Citigroup Inc ., the third-biggest
U.S. lender by assets, named  John Hastings  as chairman and chief
executive officer of its Canadian operations.  
 Hastings has been with the New York-based bank for more
than 25 years, most recently as head of the Canadian
institutional clients group, Citigroup said today in a
statement.  
 Citigroup has at least 4,600 employees in Canada. Last
month, Toronto-based Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce agreed
to buy the lenderâ€™s C$2.1 billion ($2 billion) Canadian credit-
card portfolio.  
